docs.abstract: An evil weave turns a shy character into a serial killer in “Bad Hair,” but the film doesn’t understand that styling locks can be a source of intimacy and communal pride.
docs.snippet: An evil weave turns a shy character into a serial killer in “Bad Hair,” but the film doesn’t understand that styling locks can be a source of intimacy and communal pride.
docs.lead_paragraph: Halfway through “Bad Hair,” Justin Simien’s horror-comedy on Hulu, a group of Black women sit in a conference room and debate the merits of changing their hairstyles to conform to the new corporate climate at Culture, the Black music television network where they work.

headline.main: Black Women’s Hair and Horror Movies: What Could Go Wrong?
headline.print_headline: Her Hair Is Part Of the Plot

docs.abstract: Ensembles shut by the coronavirus pandemic are shaking up their programming. Artists of color are hoping it’s for the long haul.
docs.snippet: Ensembles shut by the coronavirus pandemic are shaking up their programming. Artists of color are hoping it’s for the long haul.
docs.lead_paragraph: In June, as millions of Americans filled city streets with Black Lives Matter demonstrations and millions more rushed to share their solidarity online, the composer Jessie Montgomery noticed something unusual.

headline.main: Orchestras Are Rushing to Add Black Composers. Will It Last?

docs.abstract: Nigerians are stunned after police and soldiers opened fire on protesters against police brutality. The largely peaceful demonstrations have grown into a challenge for the government.
docs.snippet: Nigerians are stunned after police and soldiers opened fire on protesters against police brutality. The largely peaceful demonstrations have grown into a challenge for the government.
docs.lead_paragraph: LAGOS, Nigeria — With music playing and food being passed around, a festive atmosphere hung over the protest encampment on Tuesday night, despite the anger over police brutality that in recent weeks had driven youthful demonstrations that were the biggest Nigeria had seen in a generation.

headline.main: A Dozen Protesters in Nigeria Reported Killed by Security Forces
headline.print_headline: Nigeria in Shock After Police and Soldiers Fatally Shoot Protesters

docs.abstract: The Michigan city, like the state, is a battleground of cultural and racial tensions. I should know: I grew up there.
docs.snippet: The Michigan city, like the state, is a battleground of cultural and racial tensions. I should know: I grew up there.
docs.lead_paragraph: From a gauzy distance, Kevin Swift describes his high school years in the 1980s in Kalamazoo, Mich., as a carefree time of basketball games, English classes and beer parties. “We had it great there,” said Mr. Swift, who is Black and grew up in a majority-white neighborhood.

headline.main: In Kalamazoo, Old High School Classmates Reckon With a Divided Country
headline.print_headline: In Michigan, Old Classmates Reckon With a Divided Country

docs.abstract: In “Nobody Knows,” the jookin star presents a short film that explores his struggles as a Black man and his relationship to dance.
docs.snippet: In “Nobody Knows,” the jookin star presents a short film that explores his struggles as a Black man and his relationship to dance.
docs.lead_paragraph: Lil Buck, the willowy dancer who spins on the toes of his sneakers as if they were point shoes, was a little boy — probably around 6 — when a church choir filled him with such spirit that he got up and began to dance.

headline.main: Lil Buck Feels the Dancing Spirit All Over Again

docs.abstract: Since 2016, the Falun Gong-backed newspaper has used aggressive Facebook tactics and right-wing misinformation to create an anti-China, pro-Trump media empire.
docs.snippet: Since 2016, the Falun Gong-backed newspaper has used aggressive Facebook tactics and right-wing misinformation to create an anti-China, pro-Trump media empire.
docs.lead_paragraph: For years, The Epoch Times was a small, low-budget newspaper with an anti-China slant that was handed out free on New York street corners. But in 2016 and 2017, the paper made two changes that transformed it into one of the country’s most powerful digital publishers.

headline.main: How The Epoch Times Created a Giant Influence Machine
headline.print_headline: How an Obscure Newspaper Became a Bullhorn for the Far Right
